     <div type="printer_to_author">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>The aforesaid Stationers answer.</head>
   <opener>
      <salute>
         <seg rend="decorInit">L</seg>Ouing, Challenging, Threatning friend, <hi>E. W.</hi>
      </salute>
   </opener>
   <p>I pray you extend your loue so farre to your friend, and your friends friend, as to thinke that neither the first will defraud you of your borrowed Booke, nor the se<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cond expose the Author to any inconuenience. The truth is my friend, vpon the sight of this Morall, Scholasticall, Theatricall Treatise, protested that the Author should receiue much right in being thus wronged; and vpon sufficient bond vnder<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tooke to saue me harmelesse if I made it more pub<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>lique then euer was intended. And withall hee armed me with a legall defence, that, if I resto<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>red tenne sold for the principall, the Author (not<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>withstanding his modesty) could frame no iust quarrell against me or you at the barre of iustice


<pb facs="4"/>
or reputaiion. Accordingly he incouraged me (if Master Schoolemaster of <hi>Hadley</hi> should school<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap> you for promise-breach) to stop his mouth with a dozen of chi<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>ken <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>tcht vnder his owne henne.</p>
   <p>I pray <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap>
      <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>refore in stead of his owne single written Co<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>, <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> him <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>ith this packet of his owne mettall st<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>mped and multiplied by the Prin<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ters <hi>Alchimy.</hi>
   </p>
   <p>The w<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>st I <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>eare, <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap>, that hee will complaine to <hi>Apoll<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>
      </hi> o<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap> me <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> I haue proclaimed abroad his priuate Shrouing. For which I haue a defence from the Authors owne penne, that <hi>Apollos so<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>lemne v<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>tion begins with Proclamation.</hi> Act. 1. S<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>n. <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> And, I trow Proclamations are intended to fi<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap> abroad in print. So in hope that I shall receiue, if not th<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>nks, yet pardon from him. <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
         <desc>•…</desc>
      </gap>rather take, then begge, leaue to remaine still</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Yours no lesse by this, R. M.</signed>
      <dateline>
         <hi>
            <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
               <desc>•…</desc>
            </gap>ndon, Apr<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
               <desc>•…</desc>
            </gap>l, 25.</hi> 1627. F<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>om the sm<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>ll <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 word">
            <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
         </gap>
         <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>f <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>y shop, whe<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>e the <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap>uth wi<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
            <desc>•…</desc>
         </gap> blowes into <hi>Pa<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1+ letters">
               <desc>•…</desc>
            </gap>ls.</hi>
